{"_id":"1Jbpxc8bDn3JkTks","name":"Armoured Caster","permission":{"default":0,"A6DXor44iDqvvTpj":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>You have practised the delicate art of casting spells while wearing armour. The penalty you suffer to spellcasting while wearing armour and shields is reduced by 1</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spellcasting d8+, Fighting d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"5sKCzLOkrciC0X5N","name":"Henchmen","permission":{"default":0,"A6DXor44iDqvvTpj":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>Your exploits have been noticed by others, and they have come to offer you their services. You are joined by two henchmen, who will follow you in return for room and board and a cut of the treasure. The henchmen are created like starting characters, except they are Extras. Henchmen advance at half the rate of the player character, and are always one rank below the player.</p>\n<p>The henchmen are loyal to your cause and will follow you into battle with bravery and determination. They are yours to command, but will not follow suicidal orders. They will leave if they are mistreated or cheated out of their cut of the treasure.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
