{"_id":"PkbReRUYCH0mpSF0","name":"Arcane Scribe","permission":{"default":0,"A6DXor44iDqvvTpj":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>You have studied many a scroll in your time, and you have learned to copy spells from written works into your spell book. Copying a spell from a spell scroll to a spell book requires a day of uninterrupted work, after which the wizard must succeed on an Arcana roll at a penalty equal to the spell rank (-1 for Novice, -2 for Seasoned, etc.).</p>\n<p>A Failure means you need more time to understand the meaning of the spell and may attempt again after spending another day researching. On a Critical Failure, you have accidentally unleashed the magic of the scroll and suffer the effect of the spell.</p>\n<p>Making spell scrolls from spells you already know is covered by the &ldquo;Artificer&rdquo; edge in the core rulebook</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Wizard), Research d6+, Arcana d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"U3s3OH5v0xKyG5Si","name":"Improved Armoured Caster","permission":{"default":0,"A6DXor44iDqvvTpj":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>You have become even more comfortable casting spells while wearing armour. Your penalty for casting spells while wearing armour is reduced by 2 instead of one.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, Armoured Caster"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"VnhgWhHNkJK0DcWM","name":"Spellblade","permission":{"default":0,"A6DXor44iDqvvTpj":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>You have mastered the art of spell combat. You can cast a spell and perform a melee attack in the same round without incurring a multi-action penalty. You must have one hand free to do this and cannot be wielding a two-handed weapon.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spellcasting d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qk3UEM0OVGCLAaA8","name":"Turn Undead","permission":{"default":0,"A6DXor44iDqvvTpj":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>You call upon your deity to cleanse the undead before you. Turn Undead costs 1 Mana and has a range of the character&rsquo;s Spirit. All undead creatures within range must make a Spirit roll or flee from the cleric until they are out of range. If you present a holy symbol while turning, the undead suffer a -1 penalty to their Spirit roll.</p>\n<p>On a Critical Failure, the undead creature is destroyed. Wild Cards suffer an automatic Wound instead.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Cleric)."}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"zWbjtjQtCPX9JTWg","name":"Favored Enemy","permission":{"default":0,"A6DXor44iDqvvTpj":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>When this edge is taken, pick a type of creature (orcs, dragons, giants, elementals, demons, etc.). You gain a +1 bonus to parry against that type of creature, and your bonus die to damage is a d8 instead of a d6 when you hit with a raise. This edge can be taken several times, but applies to a different type of creature every time.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Monster Lore d6+, Fighting d6+ or Shooting d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
